    "summary": [
      "In December 2015, representatives from 196 nations signed the Paris Agreement at Le Bourget, France, aiming to limit global warming to 1.5°C above pre-industrial levels by 2024.",
      "The IPCC Sixth Assessment Report indicated that in 2024, global temperatures were 1.45°C above the 1850–1900 baseline, with CO₂ emissions reaching a record 37.4 gigatons in 2023 according to the Global Carbon Project led by Professor Pierre Friedlingstein.",
      "While the European Union reduced emissions by 32% since 1990 under Ursula von der Leyen's leadership, Brazil faced criticism for deforestation rates of 11,568 km² in the Amazon Basin in 2024, and India's net zero pledge by 2070 was deemed too late by climate advocates.",
      "A report from InfluenceMap found that major oil companies spent $750 million on lobbying against climate legislation between 2020 and 2024, while renewable energy capacity grew with solar power surpassing 2 terawatts globally in 2024."
    ],
