    "summary": [
      "A decade after its adoption at Le Bourget, France, on December 12, 2015, the Paris Agreement's goal to limit global warming is in jeopardy as temperatures reached 1.45°C above pre-industrial levels by 2024.",
      "Despite progress like the EU reducing emissions by 32% since 1990 under Ursula von der Leyen's European Green Deal, challenges persist with Brazil facing criticism for Amazon deforestation and India's climate neutrality target set for 2070, deemed too late by activists.",
      "InfluenceMap reported that major oil companies spent $750 million on lobbying against climate legislation from 2020 to 2024, while the upcoming COP30 in Belém, Brazil, in November 2025 is seen as a critical test of global commitment to updated Nationally Determined Contributions (NDCs).",
      "Renewable energy offers hope with solar capacity surpassing 2 terawatts globally in 2024 and significant investments by Ørsted and Iberdrola, alongside an 89% drop in battery storage costs since 2010."
    ],
